PGAT_THREAT: The establishment of clusters of weeds on the banks of the creek inhibits the flow of water during high flow events and also the stability of the creek banks
Invasion by exotic vines and woody weeds is displacing and effecting the health and extent of native vegetation which in turn is affecting habitat for local fauna and the stability of the creek banks
Through establishing native vegetation on the creek banks we hope to improve water quality

LOC_LONGITUDE: The proposed activities will occur along Stonequarry Creek (-34.1658, 150.6082), Picton and Kennedy Creek, Appin (-34.201032, 150.788709)
